<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Bella Varelis was brutally blindsided and dumped by Bachelor Locky Gilbert during the reality TV show's dramatic finale.</p>

<p>But Bella appears to have put her heartbreak aside since filming ended, and has apparently jumped head first into finding love again.</p>

<p>According to Woman's Day on Monday, the marketing manger, 26, has been spotted on dating app, Tinder.</p>

<p>Scroll down for video </p>

<p>Looking for love... again: Bachelor runner-up Bella Varelis (pictured) is 'spotted on Tinder' as Osher Gunsberg hints she's a hot pick for Bachelor in Paradise</p>

<p>A Tinder profile surfaced last week, with fans claiming they'd happily 'swipe right' to pair with Bella on the free dating service.</p>

<p>It's unclear if the profile was real, as fake and catfish accounts often are created with photos of celebrity and reality TV stars. </p>

<p>Bachelor host Osher Gunsberg also hinted the Sydney-based stunner could be headed for season four of Bachelor In Paradise. </p>

<p>'Maybe it’s not the last we’ll see of Bella': Bachelor host Osher Gunsberg (pictured) also hinted the Sydney-based stunner could be headed for season four of Bachelor In Paradise</p>

<p>'Part of me really wants to say "bula Bella" under a bure': Osher said he hoped to welcome Bella (pictured) to Paradise next season, but admitted plans were up in the air amid COVID-19</p>

<p>Discussing the finale on Channel 10's podcast The Reality Bite: Cocktails and Roses, Osher said: 'Maybe it’s not the last we’ll see of Bella.'</p>

<p>'I don’t know if we’re going to go back at any point, but part of me really wants to say "bula Bella" under a bure, but I don’t know if we’re going to do Paradise in Fiji at the moment. I don’t know what’s going to happen,' he said. </p>

<p>Osher's podcast co-host and former Bachelor In Paradise star Alisha Aitken-Radburn suggested Queensland's Noosa might make for a suitability alternative amid current coronavirus travel restrictions.   </p>

<p>Daily Mail Australia has contacted Bella Varelis for comment. </p>

<p>Keeping it local? Osher's podcast co-host and former Bachelor In Paradise star Alisha Aitken-Radburn (left) suggested Queensland's Noosa might make for a suitability alternative amid current coronavirus travel restrictions</p>

<p>Meanwhile, Locky has been flaunting his new relationship with Irena at every opportunity since breaking things off with Bella in the finale.</p>

<p>He even took a subtle jab at Bella during a hike with Irena in New South Wales on Sunday.</p>

<p>'She does hike! I'm seeing it with my own eyes!' he said, after Bella had accused Irena of lying about her love of hiking on the show. </p>

<p>The Bachelorette with sisters Elly and Becky Miles premieres on October 7 from 7:30pm on Channel 10 </p>

<p>Coming soon: The Bachelorette with sisters Elly and Becky Miles premieres on October 7 from 7:30pm on Channel 10</p>
